GRID Central Data Feed API Reference

This is GRID's references for the Central Data Feed API.

API Endpoints
https://api.grid.gg/central-data/graphql
Headers
# You may receive your API key from the GRID sales team.
X-API-Key: <YOUR_API_KEY>

Static Data Overview

The Central Data Feed is the repository of GRID's static data. The term "static data" refers to information regarding an entity not associated with in-game data. For instance, data points related to a team, such as its name, logo, branding colors, and the title in which they compete, are considered static data. These data points remain constant during a series and are not affected by any in-game events; thus, GRID categorizes them as static data.

Queries

allSeries

Description

Get multiple series by query specifications.

Response

Returns a SeriesConnection!

Arguments
Name Description
after - Cursor Cursor, after which results to query.
before - Cursor Cursor, before which results to query.
filter - SeriesFilter Filters for series results.
first - Int Amount of nodes to return starting from the beginning. Defaults to 10.
last - Int Amount of nodes to return starting from the end.
orderBy - SeriesOrderBy! Ordering of resulting series set. Default = ID
orderDirection - OrderDirection! Whether to order by ascending or descending direction. Default = ASC

Example

Query
query AllSeries(
  $after: Cursor,
  $before: Cursor,
  $filter: SeriesFilter,
  $first: Int,
  $last: Int,
  $orderBy: SeriesOrderBy!,
  $orderDirection: OrderDirection!
) {
  allSeries(
    after: $after,
    before: $before,
    filter: $filter,
    first: $first,
    last: $last,
    orderBy: $orderBy,
    orderDirection: $orderDirection
  ) {
    edges {
      cursor
      node {
        id
        externalLinks {
          dataProvider {
            ...DataProviderFragment
          }
          externalEntity {
            ...ExternalEntityFragment
          }
        }
        format {
          id
          name
          nameShortened
        }
        machineDataSource {
          id
        }
        players {
          id
          age
          externalLinks {
            ...ExternalLinkFragment
          }
          fullName
          imageUrl
          nationality {
            ...NationalityFragment
          }
          nickname
          private
          roles {
            ...PlayerRoleFragment
          }
          team {
            ...TeamFragment
          }
          title {
            ...TitleFragment
          }
          type
          updatedAt
        }
        private
        productServiceLevels {
          productName
          serviceLevel
        }
        startTimeScheduled
        streams {
          url
        }
        teams {
          baseInfo {
            ...TeamFragment
          }
          scoreAdvantage
        }
        title {
          id
          logoUrl
          name
          nameShortened
          private
        }
        tournament {
          id
          children {
            ...TournamentFragment
          }
          endDate
          externalLinks {
            ...ExternalLinkFragment
          }
          logoUrl
          name
          nameShortened
          parent {
            ...TournamentFragment
          }
          private
          prizePool {
            ...MoneyFragment
          }
          startDate
          teams {
            ...TeamFragment
          }
          titles {
            ...TitleFragment
          }
          updatedAt
          venueType
        }
        type
        updatedAt
      }
    }
    pageInfo {
      endCursor
      hasNextPage
      hasPreviousPage
      startCursor
    }
    totalCount
  }
}
Variables

  "after": "<Generated Cursor Value>",
  "before": "<Generated Cursor Value>",
  "filter": SeriesFilter,
  "first": 42,
  "last": 42,
  "orderBy": "ID",

}

    "allSeries": {
      "edges": [SeriesEdge],

contentCatalogEntities

Description

Get multiple content catalog entities by query specification.

Response

Returns a ContentCatalogEntityConnection!

Arguments
Name Description
after - Cursor Returns the elements in the list that come after the specified cursor.
before - Cursor Returns the elements in the list that come before the specified cursor.
contentCatalogVersionId - ID The content catalog version Id to search entities by. If not specified, the latest version is selected.
filter - ContentCatalogEntityFilter Filter specifications.
first - Int Number of nodes to return starting from the beginning. Defaults to 10.
last - Int Number of nodes to return starting from the end.

Example

Query
query ContentCatalogEntities(
  $after: Cursor,
  $before: Cursor,
  $contentCatalogVersionId: ID,
  $filter: ContentCatalogEntityFilter,
  $first: Int,
  $last: Int
) {
  contentCatalogEntities(
    after: $after,
    before: $before,
    contentCatalogVersionId: $contentCatalogVersionId,
    filter: $filter,
    first: $first,
    last: $last
  ) {
    edges {
      cursor
      node {
        contentCatalogVersion {
          externalLinks {
            ...ExternalLinkFragment
          }
          id
          name
          private
          publishedOn
          title {
            ...TitleFragment
          }
        }
        id
        imageUrl
        name
        private
        updatedAt
      }
    }
    pageInfo {
      endCursor
      hasNextPage
      hasPreviousPage
      startCursor
    }
    totalCount
  }
}
Variables
{
  "after": "<Generated Cursor Value>",
  "before": "<Generated Cursor Value>",
  "contentCatalogVersionId": 4,
  "filter": ContentCatalogEntityFilter,
  "first": 42,
  "last": 42
}
Response
{
  "data": {
    "contentCatalogEntities": {
      "edges": [ContentCatalogEntityEdge],
      "pageInfo": PageInfo,
      "totalCount": 42
    }
  }
}

Common Types

TournamentDescriptor

Description

A description of a tournament.

Fields
Field Name Description
endDate - Date The end date of the described tournament.
id - ID ID of this descriptor.
name - String! The name of the described tournament.
nameShortened - String The shortened name of the described tournament (max. 30 characters).
parent - TournamentDescriptor The description of the parent tournament of the described tournament.
prizePool - Money The prize pool of the described tournament in USD.
sourceId - ID The tournament identifier on the source platform.
startDate - Date The start date of the described tournament.
venueType - TournamentVenueType! The type of venue where the described tournament is held.
Example
{
  "endDate": "2007-12-03",
  "id": "12345",
  "name": "abc123",
  "nameShortened": "xyz789",
  "parent": TournamentDescriptor,
  "prizePool": Money,
  "sourceId": "12345",
  "startDate": "2007-12-03",
  "venueType": "HYBRID"
}
Common Types

TournamentVenueType

Description

Defines the venue type of a tournament.

Values
Enum Value Description

HYBRID

 The tournament has both online and LAN phases.

LAN

 The tournament is held entirely at a physical location (LAN).

ONLINE

 The tournament is held entirely online.

UNKNOWN

 The venue type is not specified.
Example
"HYBRID"
